lead_paragraph: LEAD: Fog was blamed for a 14-car pileup early today on State Highway 4 between Pittsburg and Concord, the California Highway Patrol said. The accident occurred shortly before 1 A.M. and closed two of the three westbound lanes about four miles west of here for about 90 minutes, the patrol said. ''It was a chain reaction in the fog,'' a patrol officer said.

headline.main: Fog Is Blamed for Auto Pileup
